},{"type":"text","text":" object"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"types in the GeoJSON standard, but some have nonstandard names for backwards"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"compatibility."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Although you do not create instances of this class directly, you can use its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape\/shapeWithData:encoding:error:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" factory method to create one of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"concrete subclasses of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" noted above from GeoJSON data. To access a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"shape’s attributes, use the corresponding ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNFeature","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" class instead.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can add shapes to the map by adding them to an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource"},{"type":"text","text":" object."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Configure the appearance of an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource"},{"type":"text","text":"’s or "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource"},{"type":"text","text":"’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"shapes collectively using a concrete instance of "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorStyleLay